4:
No one shall trespass into our home!
This is as far as you go!
16:
What's going on here? Did
something happen in the Silver
Woods?
19:
The trees suddenly started
attacking out of nowhere! They
refuse to accept the energies of our
sorcerers as well—
21:
But it is not only the trees that were
affected!
30: It's been overtaken by a Purger!
37:
You forget your place, wooden
puppet!
43:
This is just like what happened
before! Stella, can you do
something about it?
48: I... can't! Something is blocking me!
52: I see now what is going on!
56:
The high elves spoke of Overlord
toys like you!
63:
I need only deal with you in a more
permanent manner!
71:
Estariel, what is happening? Aren't
the high elves supposed to be
slumbering in this location?
76:
They were, though if they have
awoken, it falls to me to do deal with
them.
88:
Now that we have reached this
point, you wish to play games?
Enough.
93:
Why embroil yourself in such violent
emotions, little princess?
110:
The Silver Woods existed alongside
my very soul... The remnants of
myself left behind will never vanish
from here.
112:
I have been waiting for you to return,
Paragon of Hope.
114:
The fiends are a threat no longer.
Our haven is all but secured.
116:
Seal the Silver Woods, and let us all
slumber together—
121:
Why is that the only course you high
elves can think of?
128:
He never once called me by that
name.
133:
Rustamov is dead. Once the end
has come, it is irreversible.
136:
Those who have gone, and those
who have lived on to become new
people... They can never return to
the same place at the same point in
time.
138:
This is no different for elves. The
inevitable is simply delayed for
longer, but it is unavoidable.
141:
You could never accept that, could
you?
146:
Do you not fear death—the eternal
parting?
149:
Leave this place, ancestors. The
haven you seek, devoid of death
and partings, is for you alone...
152: Frozen in time like a painting.
169: It is over. The high elves have gone.
172:
Their souls rest in this stone, where
time does not move. It functions
similarly to a dragon's Mark.
176:
I'm always here if you need a
shoulder to lean on, Estel.
180: You take such good care of me.
188:
I have experienced the parting of
death with someone I loved dearly...
and someone less so.
191:
This pain and emptiness I feel... I'm
certain you are no stranger to it as
well.
196:
I am afraid... I threw those memories
away.
198:
But I won't abandon the ones I have
now. Not of the people buried in the
snow, the one who disappeared into
the flames...
202:
Or the one who scattered in the
morning sun.
206: I shall endeavor to do the same.
209: Let us move onward together, Stella.
214:
Forgetting someone? I may be a
mortal, but I'll be with you every step
of the way.
222:
I expect nothing less, at least until
the day even we must bid each
other farewell...
